article_title: Patrick Kennedy Backs Quartet Health As Startups In Mental Health Are Suddenly Hot

article_metadata.description: By the time he was a teenager, Patrick Kennedy was an addict. He loaded Poland Spring bottles with vodka, and camouflaged the painkiller OxyContin, known as the “hillbilly heroin,” in vials of Bayer aspirin. He suffered from anxiety, depression, and bipolar disorder. In his newly released book A Common Struggle, the [...]
